        "duration": "7 yrs 8 mos",
        "description": "# Server Operating Systems (2022 - 2025)\n\nThis group (~200 people) covers everything from Linux Userspace to the Kernel and hardware abstraction layer. We also provide the firmware, driver and userspace abstractions for Facebook's Silicon projects (Video encode, ML Inference, etc) and the software stack that supports board management (OpenBMC).\n\nIn 2024, I took on Infrastructure Efficiency as well. These teams work on everything from low-level tracing infrastructure to high-level efficiency datasets and interfaces that drive our Efficiency opportunity prioritization. \n\n# Linux Kernel (2020 - 2022)\n\nAt the end of 2020, I moved to support Facebook's server kernel efforts. Facebook employees several key maintainers of Linux subsystems including block, bpf, btrfs, cgroups, rcu, and much more. We started with a SWE team of ~15 and more than doubled it in size by establishing consistent standards for incoming leveling and recognizing open source and long-term work.\n\n# Cluster Management - Containers (2017 - 2020)\n\nI managed the engineering teams (~40 people) that own Facebook's container-heavy operating system. This includes teams focused on core container runtime, host management, host configuration, package builds and distribution, health awareness, etc.  I believe strongly in pushing our progress back to the community, so you can see my team's fingerprints on projects like buck, systemd, and the Linux kernel.",
