        "duration": "4 yrs",
        "description": "# Linux Kernel - Networking\n\nI primarily worked on readying ipvs for Facebook's IPv6-only infrastructure by adding IPv4-in-IPv6 encapsulation. All of that work was done upstream and made available for the broader community. I also designed, built, and deployed a multi-sink virtual networking solution that enabled the roll out of core infrastructure like container orchestration across Facebook's CDN network appliance. I was also responsible for identifying, debugging, and fixing various other kernel issues.\n\n# Traffic Infrastructure - CDN\n\nI designed and built the first iteration of most of Facebook's caching stack, including the caching plugin in the HTTP load balancer and the cache itself (first mcdipper, and then bigcache). I also started the Facebook Network Appliance project including building and deploying the first working prototypes within Facebook's Infrastructure.\n\n# Cache Infrastructure - Memcache\n\nI designed and implemented the first non-ascii memcache protocol used widely at Facebook which would ultimately support billions of operations per second and become the groundwork for future iterations of the protocol. I contributed to a flash-based key-value cache and adapted it to the memcache protocol, which became the foundation of our first native CDN efforts.",
